description: A framework intended to assist in the development of .Net framework web application.
summary:
This package contains dlls offering assistance building line of business apps by providing functionality addressing cross-cutting concerns, generic standard contract wcf services, restful webapi infrastructure, and data access support to several datastores.

The xf provides a generic standard contract service wherein a client simply makes a RESTfull type call for any dto or business object, and the data access code is discovered and executed at runtime using MEF.  

The xf also includes three dlls to assist in building a robust RESTfull webapi, where each api call may be logged (along with what code responded to the call).  Route handling controllers may be implemented as discoverable dlls, so that deployment may consist of simply adding dlls to a folder.

GrapeCity Spread.Services for .NET is a new small-footprint high-performance spreadsheet component. It gives developers a comprehensive API to quickly create, manipulate, convert, and share Microsoft Excel-compatible spreadsheets. Plus, you can call it from nearly any application and platform.
 
We model our interface-based API on Excel's document object model. This means that you can import, calculate, query, generate, and export any spreadsheet scenario.
 
Imported or generated spreadsheets can contain references to one another. Some of the many things you can reference include: full reports, sorted and filtered tables, sorted and filtered pivot tables, charts, sparklines, conditional formats, and dashboard reports.
 
Spread.Services targets .NET Standard 1.4 for multi-platform support including the .NET Framework, .NET Core, Mono and more. Spread.Services is the perfect solution for all of your spreadsheet challenges.

Microsoft PROgram Synthesis using Examples SDK (PROSE) tools for compiling DSLs into program synthesis libraries.
summary: Library for automatically synthesizing programs from examples.

description:
Library for automatically synthesizing programs from examples.

Microsoft PROgram Synthesis using Examples SDK (PROSE) is a framework of technologies for automatic generation of programs from input-output examples, keywords, and similar forms of imprecise specification. In PROSE, you define a domain-specific language (DSL) of programs that constitute your domain of useful tasks (e.g. a DSL of CSS selectors). At runtime, you give PROSE some (typically user-provided) input-output examples for the desired program's behavior, and its algorithms synthesize a ranked set of programs from this DSL that are consistent with the given examples. These programs can be saved and applied on similar user data after one learning session (typically with 1-4 examples). PROSE can be used to enable programming-by-example experience in an arbitrary user-facing application, provided the app developer describes its application domain in a DSL form.

As part of the project, the PROSE framework includes a set of specific technologies for various data wrangling domains. These include Transformation.Text, a library of string transformations first shipped as FlashFill in Microsoft Excel 2013, text extraction library with a DSL of programs that find a desired sequence of regions in a textual file, and several others. All of these data wrangling libraries, as well as the underlying program synthesis framework, can currently be used out of the box for research, education, and other non-commercial initiatives.
